snippet.title: Judge Gives Johnny Depp Access To Amber Heard’s Phone Records And This Happens
snippet.description:
Judge Gives Johnny Depp Access To Amber Heard’s Phone Records And This Happens
Subscribe to Binge Watch -  http://tiny.cc/bingewatch

WATCH NEXT 👇🏻

How Amber Heard Destroyed Her Own Career
https://youtu.be/gEfWUbRfFR8

Related videos:

"She's Done" Judge Reveals Giving Johnny Depp Access To Amber Heard's Phone Records
https://youtu.be/EByDV-bbgTI


In this installment, we'll finally reveal if Amber Heard's bruises were fake or not!
Can’t wait to know the truth? I bet! So, make sure you stay till the end of the video.
They say nothing lasts forever and Amber Heard and Johnny Depp’s court case seems to be finalized soon. And not in Amber Heard’s favor. Recently, a Virginia judge ruled Johnny Depp’s legal team can have an expert look at Amber Heard’s phone records and other devices to examine if the photos with bruises were fabricated.
According to Johnny Depp and his legal team, Amber Heard faked the photos of herself having a black eye and claimed it was Johnny Depp who did that to her back in 2015 to ruin his life and career. Johnny Depp’s lawyer, Benjamin Chew, alleged to the Circuit Court of Fairfax Country in a court filing that “Ms. Heard’s counsel has repeatedly used these phony photographs at deposition”.
Also, JD is convinced that it would be possible to prove that Amber faked photos because even the police officers who responded to the 2015 incident between Johnny Depp and Amber Heard, “found no injury upon Ms. Heard and no disruption to the penthouses." This information was published by Page Six as well. Page Six also published the information that JD's attorney, Benjamin Chew,
alleged in his court filing. The statement said: "Ms. Heard and her friends then fabricated photos that she used to obtain an ex parte TRO [temporary restraining order] and a $7 million divorce settlement".
But not only the police officers and Johnny Depp can confirm that Amber Heard actually was safe and sound and had no injuries. Amber’s former friend Laura Divenere, who furnished the ex-couple's Los Angeles penthouse, said in her witness statement she never saw Amber Heard with any injuries. She even claimed
in her written statement that Amber Heard never spoke about being the victim of domestic abuse in her relationship with Johnny Depp. Moreover, Laura was there with Amber after the alleged fight and she officially confirmed that Amber was
alright. In her testimony to the US court, Laura said: “On those days, I worked with Amber, retrieved packages for her, rode elevators with her, and saw her up close in person.”
“On none of those days immediately following the abuse claims did I observe any signs of physical abuse or injury, including redness, swelling, cuts, bruising, or damage of any kind. I never saw Amber injured in any way, although I am now aware that she has had many abuse claims”.
Another person, who clearly confirmed that Amber’s face didn’t have any injuries, was her makeup artist and stylist, Samantha McMillan. She said: “Throughout the day of December 16, 2015, I could see clearly that Amber Heard did not have any visible marks, bruises, cuts, or injuries to her face or any other part of her body”. Moreover, Amber Heard appeared on James Corden's US TV show the day after the alleged attack and said none of her injuries were visible because they were covered with make-up. Well, hardly the makeup can cover the injuries Amber
Heard allegedly had. She told the court she had "two black eyes, a broken nose and
broken lip, bruises all over my body, bruises on my forearm". "I think I had bruises
on my chin, chunks of my hair were missing, pus was in the wounds on my
hairline," she alleged. What kind of makeup can help with that?
A tape of her appearance on the show was played in court and Eleanor Laws QC, for Depp, asked Heard: "That's what you looked like on the show. There is no sign of you having any injuries." Amber Heard replied: "I have tons of injuries." Ms Laws then said, "You don't have a split lip", and Heard replied, "Of course I do," adding she "caked on red lipstick" and "caked on makeup" to cover her injuries.

snippet.title: Amber Heard - The aqua queen.
snippet.description:
Amber Heard biography,age,family,income and early life.

Hello friends, Welcome to our business one channel, How are doing today. Lets get started
Amber Laura Heard was born on April 22, 1986 is an American film and television actress.
 After a series of small roles in film and television, Amber Heard had her first starring role in the horror film All the Boys Love Mandy Lane (2006).
Amber Heard first gained mainstream recognition for supporting roles in the action film Never Back Down (2008) and the comedy Pineapple Express (2008).
In the following years, Amber Heard appeared in films such as The Joneses (2009), The Ward (2010), The Rum Diary (2011), Drive Angry (2011), Machete Kills (2013) and Magic Mike XXL (2015).
In 2017, Amber Heard joined the DC Extended Universe to play Atlantean queen Mera in superhero films Justice League (2017), Aquaman (2018), and Zack Snyder's Justice League (2021).
In addition to acting, Amber Heard has been a global spokesperson for the cosmetics giant L'Oréal Paris since 2018. Amber Heard also engages in human rights activism.
Amber Heard was married to actor Johnny Depp from 2015 to 2017. Their divorce drew significant media attention as Amber Heard alleged that he had been abusive through most of their relationship. 
Johnny Depp then sued her for defamation in 2019 after Amber Heard  wrote an op-ed discussing being a public victim of domestic violence. 
Johnny Depp also sued the publishers of The Sun in a related libel suit in England. 

In 2020, the High Court of Justice of England and Wales ruled that Johnny Depp had lost his libel case and that the majority of Heard's allegations had been proven to a civil standard.
Amber Heard was born in Austin, Texas, to Patricia Paige, an internet researcher (1956–2020), and David Clinton Heard (born 1950), who owned a small construction company.
Amber Heard earliest acting work included appearances in two music videos, Kenny Chesney's "There Goes My Life" and Eisley's "I Wasn't Prepared", and small supporting roles in the television series Jack & Bobby (2004), The Mountain (2004), and The O.C. (2005).

Amber Heard gained moderate mainstream recognition in 2008 with supporting roles in the Judd Apatow-produced stoner comedy Pineapple Express and the martial arts drama Never Back Down, both of which were box office successes. 
In 2017, Amber Heard appeared as part of an ensemble cast in Lake Bell's indie comedy I Do... Until I Don't and joined the DC Extended Universe (DCEU) cast as Mera, Aquaman's Atlantean queen, in the superhero film Justice League.
Amber Heard is an ambassador for the American Civil Liberties Union (ACLU), to whom Amber Heard pledged half of her divorce settlement, and a Human Rights Champion for the Stand Up for Human Rights campaign by the Office of the United Nations High Commissioner for Human Rights.
Amber Heard publicly came out in 2010, but has stated, "I don't label myself one way or another—I have had successful relationships with men and now a woman. 
Amber Heard and Johnny Depp began dating in 2012 and were married in a civil ceremony in February 2015. In April 2015, Heard breached Australia's biosecurity laws when she failed to declare her and Depp's two dogs to the customs when they flew into Queensland, where he was working on a film.
Amber Heard pleaded guilty to falsifying quarantine documents, stating that she had made a mistake due to sleep deprivation.
Hope you guys are enjoying my videos, Please do not forget to subscribe our channel  for upcoming videos, We appreciate your view and being our valued viewer, have a nice day and stay safe.

snippet.title: Amber Heard is the Problem not Johnny Depp
snippet.description:
A judge has granted Johnny Depp access to his ex-wife Amber Heard's phone, which he claims will show she lied about injuries he allegedly caused her.

The "Pirates of the Caribbean" star, who is suing Heard for $50 million in libel, alleges she doctored images purporting to depict her with two black eyes, which she claims she sustained at the hands of the actor in 2015.

"Ms. Heard's counsel has frequently presented these false images during deposition," Depp's lawyer Benjamin Chew said in a court filing to the Circuit Court of Fairfax County, Va.

Depp, 58, is suing Heard, 35, in Virginia for an op-ed she penned in the Washington Post in 2019 about domestic abuse — but which he says was a defamatory assault on him.

snippet.title: Tallow and Marty Timelapse (Amber Haze)
snippet.description:
Marty - “Señorita Tallow. If I may ask. What do you expect to find here in Kilbrook pass? I’ve heard that it’s $10,000 for your head. If you’re looking for refuge, I’m afraid you’ve come to the wrong place, mi cariño.”

Tallow - “Lawmen sniff around here often?”

Marty - “Not lawmen… Redtowns. I suggest you keep your head down, ¿vale?”

Tallow - “I’ll take that into heart, amigo.”

Marty - “I’m flattered that you think we are friends. I cannot seem to think of anyone else I’ve been able to say that to. At least not any more…”

Tallow - “Well, friends are useful in a place like this, don’t ya think?”

Marty - “Well, Ms Tallow. There’s a difference between those who are truly your friend and those who just want to use you. Friends don’t have a ‘use’. Friends have a purpose. And that purpose is to be your friend.”

Marty and Tallow meet in person for the first time to share a nice conversation. Considering that Marty is older and wiser than Tallow, he shares his wisdom with her about living off the land and how she should handle relationships. They meet in the desert town of Kilbrook pass, which lawmen know as the town which houses the deadliest outlaws. Many lawmen refuse to investigate due to their lack of jurisdiction and gun power. Many detectives from private agencies sniff around, so outlaws in this town have to be careful about who they speak to.

Song: Bjorn Olsson - Annika

snippet.title: Are Ty Borden & Amy Fleming a Couple in Real Life? The FACTS
snippet.description:
We're discussing Heartland TV Show's main cast members, Amber Marshall and Graham Wardle aka Amy Fleming and Ty Borden. Heartland has been a part of our lives for the past 15 years. Sometimes, we feel like we grew up with them. When Ty Borden died, Amy Fleming is left alone as a single mother, which felt so unfair for many fans. For many, it was almost certain that Amy and Ty will inherit the Heartland ranch one day but now, with the death of Ty Borden, everything became ambiguous. Suddenly, we struggled in having any idea about what will happen next in the show. A considerable amount of fans, however, were okay with losing Ty. “Why?” you may ask.
